Decades of research in computer animation (e.g., 
[Witkin and Kass 1988; Cohen 1992; Liu et al. 1994; Fang and Pollard 2003]
) introduced numerous performance criteria for human motion modeling, e.g., minimal energy, minimal torque, minimal jerk, minimal joint momentum, minimal joint acceleration, or minimal torque change.

